==Trivia==
*In the comics, Michael Morbius is a Nobel Prize-winning biochemist suffering from a blood disease, who became the anti-hero known as '''Morbius the Living Vampire''', who originally fought [[Spider-Man]] as a villain before becoming an anti-hero instead.
*Morbius was hinted in ''[[Venom: Let There Be Carnage]]'', through a [[Living Vampires|Living Vampire]] engraving shown on [[Cletus Kasady]]'s [[San Quentin State Prison|cell]].<ref>[[:File:VENOM- LET THERE BE CARNAGE - Cletus' Cell - Easter Eggs|''VENOM: LET THERE BE CARNAGE'' - Cletus' Cell | Easter Eggs]]</ref>
*According to [[Martine Bancroft]], Michael's password for everything is the first six digits of {{WPS|π (number)|π}}, backwards (951413).
*Morbius is a fan of the film ''[https://m.imdb.com/title/tt0075802/ Palace Carnage]''.
*Morbius likes spicy {{WPS|Cheetos}}.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Greg Townley]], [[Vinny O'Brien]] and [[Andrew James Bleidner]] were stunt doubles for [[Jared Leto]] in the role of Morbius.
*This is the second live incarnation of Morbius, followed by an incarnation portray by {{WPS|Stephen Norrington}} in a deleted scene in {{WPS|Blade (1998 film)|Blade}}.
**A deleted scene in the end of Blade shows a man wearing all-black cloth, a black helmet and a cape standing on top of a building is intended to be Morbius. But unfortunately this never happened, as {{WPS|New Line Cinema}} never owns the right of the character.
**Morbius is also being planned to be the main villain of {{WPS|Blade II}}, but unfortunately never happened.

